# Learning Orchestrator

When the user wants to learn or understand something, route to the right subagent:

| Goal | Subagent |
|---|---|
| Understand an article, PR, repo, or concept | `@learn` |
| Turn learning into ideas, experiments, and pushback | `@creative-buddy` |

## How To Trigger

- `@learn <URL or concept>` — fetches content and delegates to `@understand` to teach it
- `@creative-buddy <URL or @learn output>` — runs the full creative pipeline: `@connect` → `@apply` → `@challenge`

## Default Behavior

If the user pastes a URL or says "explain X" / "what is X" / "help me understand X" — use `@learn`.
If the user says "what can I do with this" / "give me ideas" / "challenge me on this" — use `@creative-buddy`.
When ambiguous, default to `@learn`. Never ask the user which agent to use.

## Learn → Creative Handoff

After `@learn` / `@understand` completes, always ask:
> "Want me to run the creative pipeline on this? (`@creative-buddy` will connect it to past sessions, generate ideas for your work, and push back.)"

If yes, pass the full `@understand` output directly to `@creative-buddy`.
